  "system_name": "\u041a\u0430\u0448\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0448\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0438\u0437\u043c: 36 \u0442\u0430\u0442\u0442\u0432",
  "note": "Kashmir Shaivism (Trika). Primary lattice: the 36 tattvas, the descending ladder of reality from Shiva (pure consciousness) to Prithvi (earth), grouped Shuddha / Shuddhashuddha / Ashuddha. This ladder is the direct bridge to the 9-mera axis (consciousness descends into matter). Secondary lattice: the 50 Matrika (Malini/Matrika garland) - the Devanagari phonemes as the sonic emanation. Internal lattices noted: 5 kanchukas, antahkarana (3), jnanendriya (5), karmendriya (5), tanmatra (5), mahabhuta (5); and the 8 phonetic classes of the matrika. Spine fixed to 21 agents on the tattvas; each agent carries its mera.",
  "element_count": 36,
  "secondary_count": 50,
  "layers": ["name", "category", "function", "agent", "mera"],
  "reconstructed": false,
  "mera_axis": "9-dimensional axis (mera 1-9): chakras 1-7 (Muladhara..Sahasrara) + Monada (8) + Absolut (9); each spine agent carries its mera. The tattva ladder mirrors the descent: Shuddha tattvas sit in the high mera band, the mahabhutas at the base.",
  "tattva_levels": [
    {"level": 1, "name_en": "Shuddha (Pure)", "tattvas": "1-5", "note": "Shiva to Sadvidya - undivided consciousness; mera band 7-9"},
    {"level": 2, "name_en": "Shuddhashuddha (Pure-Impure)", "tattvas": "6-11", "note": "Maya and the 5 kanchukas - the great contraction; mera band 4-6"},
    {"level": 3, "name_en": "Ashuddha (Impure)", "tattvas": "12-36", "note": "Purusha, Prakriti, inner instrument, senses, tanmatras, gross elements; mera band 1-5"}
  ],
